newsitem.title: ARGENTINA: Argentine Oct industrial output up 11.3 pct - FIEL.
newsitem.headline: Argentine Oct industrial output up 11.3 pct - FIEL.

text.p: Argentina's industrial production in October was 11.3 percent higher than in October 1995, the private consultancy FIEL said Monday.
In a preliminary report issued last week, the group had estimated 11.7 growth.
Compared with September, industrial output rose 4.3 percent, FIEL said Monday.
Minutes earlier Economic Planning Secretary Eugenio Pendaz told reporters that the government was expecting October industrial production to grow "more than 12 percent" from October 1995.
FIEL said October was the seventh consecutive month of industrial production growth following a year-long recession induced by the "Tequila effect" of Mexico's December 1994 peso devaluation.
